properties.areaDesc: Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 13 at 8:48PM MST until February 15 at 6:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 MPH with gusts up to 70 MPH. Periods
of blowing snow are also possible.

* WHERE...Interstate 25 between Chugwater and Wheatland.

* WHEN...From 11 PM tonight until 6 PM MST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Expect dangerous travel for
light, high profile vehicles including camping and tractor
trailers. There will be a high risk for blow overs of these
types of vehicles. Periods of blowing snow may significantly
reduce visibilities and create slick road conditions.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected
or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 mph or gusts of
58 mph or more can lead to property damage.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM MST SATURDAY
